<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-008-396 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 510 970</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  Nov 22 1991 v141 pC2(N) pD2(L) 9 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Emergency phone plan by Dinkins panel.(New York City Mayor DavidN. Dinkins)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ramirez, Anthony.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>New York City Mayor David N. Dinkins announces a first-of-its-kindtelephone disaster recovery plan that would help restore servicesfaster in cases such as the four system breakdowns experienced byATandamp;T since Jan 1990.andP;  The plan would allow telephone carriersexperiencing system breakdowns to declare an emergency and contactone of thirteen other New York and New Jersey carriers to supportits customers for up to seven weeks.andP;  The plan does not cover suchbasic problems as computer software failures that can cause asystem breakdown in .01 seconds.andP;  Carriers participating in theplan include ATandamp;T, MCI Communications Corp, and the New York andNew Jersey Bell Telephone Companies, among others.andP;  The plan'sdetails are still to be approved by the carriers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Planning)MCI Communications Corp. (Planning)New York Telephone Co. (Planning)New Jersey Telephone Co. (Planning).andO;Topic:     Disaster PlanningDisaster ManagementTelephone companiesMunicipal GovernmentNew York.andO;Person:    Dinkins, David N. (Science and technology policy).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>